## 🔑 Summary

```
Single Thread Program:

1 Process created       → JVM process (PID)
6 Threads created       → 1 main + 5 JVM background
1 Object in Heap        → MusicPlayer object
1 Stack                 → main thread stack only

Methods run:
playSong()     → 0s  to 5s   (5s)
downloadSong() → 5s  to 13s  (8s)
likeSong()     → 13s to 15s  (2s)

Total = 15 seconds

Problem:
→ Sequential execution
→ CPU blocked during sleep/IO
→ No parallelism
→ Slow and inefficient

Solution → Multithreading! 🚀
```

